1
00:00:14,203 --> 00:00:16,501
Whoo!

2
00:00:42,097 --> 00:00:47,467
You know, showboating like that
just makes you look desperate.

3
00:00:47,503 --> 00:00:51,269
Yeah, "Look at me. I can flip my ski."
Pathetic.

4
00:00:51,307 --> 00:00:54,401
- Yeah.
- Daniel, that was awesome!

5
00:00:55,444 --> 00:00:57,708
Nicole.

6
00:01:01,483 --> 00:01:03,644
Hey, Daniel, Nicole left, huh?

7
00:01:03,686 --> 00:01:06,814
Should've let me talk to her.

8
00:01:12,628 --> 00:01:14,493
Whoo-hoo!

9
00:01:21,603 --> 00:01:23,093
I love it out here.

10
00:01:26,642 --> 00:01:30,078
The Big Dipper.
It's my favorite.

11
00:01:32,047 --> 00:01:33,742
- Do you know that one?
- No.

12
00:01:33,816 --> 00:01:36,546
I got a D in Astronomy.

13
00:01:40,656 --> 00:01:43,557
So, I never see you with anyone.

14
00:01:43,625 --> 00:01:47,026
Do you have a girlfriend
out of town or something?

15
00:01:54,002 --> 00:01:56,095
Daniel? Daniel?

16
00:02:02,845 --> 00:02:06,042
I want you to feel this!

17
00:02:07,383 --> 00:02:10,784
This is what's coming for you.

18
00:02:13,989 --> 00:02:15,115
Daniel, are you OK?

19
00:02:17,326 --> 00:02:18,918
Oh, my God.

20
00:02:23,732 --> 00:02:26,929
He's a freak.
He's some kind of freak.

21
00:03:12,714 --> 00:03:13,942
Number Three's dead.

22
00:03:15,517 --> 00:03:17,951
You all right?

23
00:03:18,987 --> 00:03:21,820
- Yeah.
- Anyone else see what happened?

24
00:04:02,464 --> 00:04:06,366
I told you not to keep this crap.
It just slows us down.

25
00:04:33,228 --> 00:04:34,957
All right, let's go.

26
00:04:42,471 --> 00:04:43,938
Daniel.

27
00:04:51,079 --> 00:04:54,879
<i>This is the part
I hate the most, the running.</i>

28
00:04:54,917 --> 00:04:58,182
<i>But it's the only thing
in my life that's real.</i>

29
00:04:58,220 --> 00:05:00,051
<i>The rest is a lie.</i>

30
00:05:00,088 --> 00:05:02,283
<i>Even Henri.</i>

31
00:05:02,357 --> 00:05:04,257
<i>People think he's my father.</i>

32
00:05:04,293 --> 00:05:05,920
<i>He's not.</i>

33
00:05:05,961 --> 00:05:10,523
<i>He's a warrior from my planet,
assigned to keep me alive.</i>

34
00:05:11,833 --> 00:05:14,063
<i>I don't remember my father.</i>

35
00:05:14,102 --> 00:05:17,265
<i>All he left for me
was some kind of box.</i>

36
00:05:17,306 --> 00:05:20,070
<i>Henri says he'll pass it on to me
when the time is right.</i>

37
00:05:22,778 --> 00:05:25,872
<i>I got my first scar
when I was nine years old,</i>

38
00:05:25,914 --> 00:05:28,439
<i>near the border of Mexico.</i>

39
00:05:28,517 --> 00:05:31,281
<i>It woke me from my sleep.</i>

40
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:35,347
<i>It was the first sign that the
Mogadorians had found us here on Earth.</i>

41
00:05:36,191 --> 00:05:39,126
<i>The second scar
came when I was 12.</i>

42
00:05:39,194 --> 00:05:42,493
<i>I was in Colorado,
in the middle of a spelling bee.</i>

43
00:05:43,465 --> 00:05:46,696
<i>As soon as I felt it,
I knew Number Two was dead.</i>

44
00:05:47,936 --> 00:05:50,700
<i>Last night, I got my third scar.</i>

45
00:05:53,442 --> 00:05:58,311
<i>I was just a kid when the Mogadorians
invaded my planet, Lorien.</i>

46
00:05:58,347 --> 00:06:00,815
<i>Nine of us children escaped.</i>

47
00:06:00,882 --> 00:06:05,319
<i>We were gifted, meant to protect
our people when we grew up.</i>

48
00:06:05,354 --> 00:06:09,051
<i>We never got the chance.
Everyone was killed.</i>

49
00:06:10,292 --> 00:06:13,159
<i>We are the last of our kind.</i>

50
00:06:13,228 --> 00:06:17,460
<i>Three of us are gone. Dead.</i>

51
00:06:17,499 --> 00:06:20,730
<i>They are hunting us down,
one by one, in order.</i>

52
00:06:22,571 --> 00:06:24,334
<i>I know I'm next.</i>

53
00:06:26,108 --> 00:06:27,507
<i>I am Number Four.</i>

54
00:06:27,576 --> 00:06:28,873
All right, well, so...

55
00:06:28,944 --> 00:06:31,845
Daniel won't be in school
the rest of the semester.

56
00:06:31,913 --> 00:06:34,381
OK. You, too.

57
00:06:36,385 --> 00:06:37,750
Your new ID.

58
00:06:38,587 --> 00:06:43,024
And this time, you stay out of sight,
huh? No school, no teams, nothing.

59
00:06:43,058 --> 00:06:45,049
John Smith. Very original.

60
00:06:45,127 --> 00:06:48,290
I don't want to be original.
I want to be invisible.

61
00:06:52,134 --> 00:06:54,295
This time was different.

62
00:06:54,336 --> 00:06:56,327
I didn't just get a scar.

63
00:06:56,371 --> 00:06:58,965
I, uh... I saw Number Three.

64
00:07:01,043 --> 00:07:04,706
I felt the knife, I felt him die.
I could tell we all did.

65
00:07:05,947 --> 00:07:09,314
- The others.
- We should get moving.

66
00:07:09,351 --> 00:07:12,013
Mogadorians could've
already picked up our scent.

67
00:07:13,321 --> 00:07:17,121
We're going to Paradise.
I have business to take care of.

68
00:08:25,827 --> 00:08:26,953
It's Bernie Kosar.

69
00:08:28,930 --> 00:08:30,397
Played football.

70
00:08:34,102 --> 00:08:38,266
- Yeah, he played for Cleveland.
- Hm. Good to know.

71
00:08:38,306 --> 00:08:41,070
- Next time, I get to pick the place.
- Yeah.

72
00:09:12,874 --> 00:09:15,536
That's all of it.
I'm going to bed.

73
00:09:15,610 --> 00:09:19,205
Ooh. Hang on.
I need a new picture.

74
00:09:20,515 --> 00:09:23,006
We have to wipe out anything
that hits the Internet.

75
00:09:23,084 --> 00:09:26,383
Say "Paradise."

76
00:09:32,460 --> 00:09:33,484
Oh, shit.

77
00:09:33,528 --> 00:09:35,723
This is why
I need you to be invisible.

78
00:10:07,262 --> 00:10:08,286
Get back inside.

79
00:10:10,232 --> 00:10:11,597
John.

80
00:10:11,666 --> 00:10:15,193
Come on. Come back inside.

81
00:10:24,746 --> 00:10:27,909
Little small for a Mogadorian,
don't you think?

82
00:10:30,285 --> 00:10:32,116
I'm sure he belongs to someone.

83
00:10:32,187 --> 00:10:35,281
He doesn't
have any collar or tags.

84
00:10:35,357 --> 00:10:37,917
Hm. Somebody, somewhere,
must miss you, huh?

85
00:10:40,929 --> 00:10:42,328
Come on.

86
00:10:42,397 --> 00:10:45,093
Another pair of eyes
and ears watching the house?

87
00:10:45,834 --> 00:10:49,133
- I'm gonna need somebody to talk to.
- Talk to me.

88
00:10:51,539 --> 00:10:53,439
Yeah, keep the dog.

89
00:10:53,508 --> 00:10:54,907
What are you gonna call him?

90
00:10:56,311 --> 00:10:59,246
How about Bernie Kosar?

91
00:12:36,478 --> 00:12:38,207
What are you doing up?

92
00:12:38,279 --> 00:12:39,871
I changed my mind.

93
00:12:39,948 --> 00:12:41,779
About what?

94
00:12:41,850 --> 00:12:44,910
Look, uh, as much fun
as you are to be around,

95
00:12:44,953 --> 00:12:48,013
I can't be a prisoner.
Uh, I have to go to school.

96
00:12:48,056 --> 00:12:50,081
- No. No way, too risky.
- Come on.

97
00:12:50,158 --> 00:12:52,683
Number Three was completely
off the grid and the Mogs got him.

98
00:12:52,727 --> 00:12:54,251
- Didn't save him.
- Mm-mm.

99
00:12:54,329 --> 00:12:57,890
Come on.
I'm gonna be safer if I blend in.

100
00:12:57,966 --> 00:12:59,433
I promise I'll keep a low profile.

101
00:12:59,501 --> 00:13:01,662
Look. Even if I let you, and I'm not,

102
00:13:01,703 --> 00:13:03,933
you can't just waltz into school
and start class...

103
00:13:04,005 --> 00:13:06,599
Do you think you're the only one
who can forge documents?

104
00:13:07,876 --> 00:13:10,344
Hm. Do you have a...?

105
00:13:10,378 --> 00:13:13,006
Five days of rations,
spare clothes, GPS, cash.

106
00:13:14,449 --> 00:13:15,711
- What's your name?
- John Smith.

107
00:13:15,750 --> 00:13:17,274
- Where are you from?
- Toronto.

108
00:13:17,352 --> 00:13:19,252
You seem kind of tan for Toronto.

109
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:23,484
Santa Fe, New Mexico.
I know the drill, OK?

110
00:13:27,929 --> 00:13:29,453
You keep this on you.
I'll call you every hour.

111
00:13:29,531 --> 00:13:31,123
If you don't pick up,
I know something's wrong.

112
00:13:31,199 --> 00:13:34,396
- Come on, every hour?
- That, or you can home school.

113
00:13:34,436 --> 00:13:36,461
And I'll be your teacher.

114
00:13:37,605 --> 00:13:38,970
Fine.

115
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:42,942
Hey, John, don't be stupid.
You keep your head down.

116
00:13:43,011 --> 00:13:44,387
I know how to blend in.

117
00:14:07,102 --> 00:14:08,467
OK, doll. Take a seat.

118
00:14:08,503 --> 00:14:10,971
I'll just print up your schedule.
Back in a jiffy.

119
00:14:14,843 --> 00:14:16,470
I know she's
the star photographer,

120
00:14:16,511 --> 00:14:18,411
but it's not fair
to the other students.

121
00:14:18,446 --> 00:14:20,107
She's using up all the vital supplies.

122
00:14:20,148 --> 00:14:23,982
Emory, come on. "Strangers in
Paradise." At least she's creative.

123
00:14:24,052 --> 00:14:26,543
The pictures on her website
are totally inappropriate.

124
00:14:26,621 --> 00:14:30,113
Mr. Behrman, if you want to keep
the photos, you should just say so.

125
00:14:30,158 --> 00:14:32,558
Keep the photos?
They're already all over the Internet!

126
00:14:32,627 --> 00:14:35,994
It's a violation to post things like
this without people's permission.

127
00:14:36,064 --> 00:14:37,361
You have to do something about this.

128
00:14:37,432 --> 00:14:39,866
Mr. Behrman,
excuse us for a few minutes, OK?

129
00:14:47,442 --> 00:14:50,843
Sarah, this is not like you.

130
00:14:50,879 --> 00:14:53,313
Is there something going on?

131
00:14:53,348 --> 00:14:56,249
- Everything's fine.
- Sarah?

132
00:14:56,317 --> 00:14:59,309
- Honestly.
- Have a seat.

133
00:15:00,188 --> 00:15:03,487
You can't let a few negative students
get you down.

134
00:15:03,525 --> 00:15:07,325
Look, I don't want you to isolate
yourself from the rest of the school.

135
00:15:07,362 --> 00:15:12,390
- You should enjoy this year.
- OK, I'll try.

136
00:15:12,467 --> 00:15:15,561
- Good.
- Can I please have my camera back?

137
00:15:15,637 --> 00:15:19,266
No more photos on your website
without teacher and student permission.

138
00:15:19,340 --> 00:15:21,035
OK.

139
00:15:21,109 --> 00:15:22,804
Here's your schedule.

140
00:15:26,314 --> 00:15:30,045
Homeroom is calculus.
That's B-wing, room seven...

141
00:15:30,118 --> 00:15:35,886
Oh, Sarah! Could you show our friend
to his locker? He's from Santa Fe.

142
00:15:35,924 --> 00:15:40,418
<i>Job fair starts tomorrow.
Everybody, job fair starts tomorrow.</i>

143
00:15:40,495 --> 00:15:43,589
What kind of camera do you use?

144
00:15:44,499 --> 00:15:46,865
Eavesdropping?
That's not gonna win you friends.

145
00:15:46,901 --> 00:15:48,528
- Check it out.
- What?

146
00:15:49,871 --> 00:15:52,704
Tell that to the principal
with a fish tank for an office.

147
00:15:53,408 --> 00:15:55,933
It's kind of hard not to hear.

148
00:15:57,245 --> 00:16:01,443
Sorry. This whole place
is kind of a fish tank.

149
00:16:02,417 --> 00:16:04,908
Well...
Room seven is down the hall,

150
00:16:04,953 --> 00:16:07,581
and, uh, that's your locker right there.

151
00:16:09,524 --> 00:16:12,652
Good luck... um...

152
00:16:12,727 --> 00:16:14,524
Oh, uh, John...

153
00:16:14,562 --> 00:16:16,655
...Smith.

154
00:16:18,433 --> 00:16:21,732
OK. You don't want to tell me your name.

155
00:16:21,769 --> 00:16:22,793
That's fine.

156
00:16:29,711 --> 00:16:33,147
That's really my name.
John Smith.

157
00:16:42,390 --> 00:16:44,950
What's up, man? You new?

158
00:16:46,527 --> 00:16:50,827
Mark James. This is Kevin,
Jackson, Tyler and Max.

159
00:16:50,898 --> 00:16:52,627
- Hey, man, what's up?
- John.

160
00:16:52,667 --> 00:16:54,635
Good to meet you, John.
Where are you from?

161
00:16:54,669 --> 00:16:57,638
- Santa Fe.
- Oh, New Mexico.

162
00:16:57,672 --> 00:16:59,003
Play any ball out there?

163
00:16:59,073 --> 00:17:01,633
- Football?
- Yeah.

164
00:17:01,676 --> 00:17:04,270
- No.
- Play anything?

165
00:17:04,312 --> 00:17:06,473
Baseball? Soccer? Ping-pong?

166
00:17:06,547 --> 00:17:08,981
Nope.

167
00:17:09,017 --> 00:17:12,612
OK. No, that's cool, man.
That's totally cool.

168
00:17:12,654 --> 00:17:14,622
We could always use more
boosters in the stands, right?

169
00:17:14,656 --> 00:17:18,956
Listen. You need anything,
you ask us, OK?

170
00:17:18,993 --> 00:17:22,019
- We got you.
- I'll keep that in mind.

171
00:17:22,096 --> 00:17:26,590
Good talking to you, big guy.

172
00:17:27,268 --> 00:17:28,633
Look who it is.

173
00:17:28,670 --> 00:17:30,865
Watch out, man.

174
00:17:30,938 --> 00:17:32,530
Sorry, Sam.

175
00:17:32,607 --> 00:17:36,543
Loser!

176
00:17:39,013 --> 00:17:40,207
Wait up, fool.

177
00:17:40,281 --> 00:17:41,543
Thanks.

178
00:17:43,318 --> 00:17:44,910
Gotta love the classics.

179
00:17:44,986 --> 00:17:47,750
Homecoming king versus
the science nerd.

180
00:17:49,324 --> 00:17:51,815
Just get better with time, don't they?

181
00:17:51,859 --> 00:17:55,351
- That guy, Mark, he's...
- Soon to be irrelevant.

182
00:17:55,396 --> 00:17:57,887
He's in the third year of
the best four years of his life.

183
00:19:00,528 --> 00:19:04,624
So, she was like, "The solar system's
sun does not revolve around the Earth."

184
00:19:04,699 --> 00:19:06,633
I said, "Yeah, right."

185
00:19:09,570 --> 00:19:10,935
Hey, Spock!

186
00:19:11,005 --> 00:19:13,769
- Nailed it!
- Heads up! UFO, brother!

187
00:19:13,808 --> 00:19:16,140
That had to hurt.

188
00:19:16,210 --> 00:19:17,939
Hey, stay down, man.
Just stay down.

189
00:19:18,012 --> 00:19:19,172
He's gonna cry. He's gonna cry.

190
00:19:19,247 --> 00:19:21,715
- Oh, Mommy's coming!
- Oh...

191
00:19:24,051 --> 00:19:26,315
- Right in the face.
- Hey, are you OK?

192
00:19:26,387 --> 00:19:30,289
- Assholes.
- Yo, new dude! Little help?

193
00:19:40,134 --> 00:19:42,068
Jesus!

194
00:19:42,103 --> 00:19:44,230
I'm fine! Get off me.

195
00:19:44,305 --> 00:19:46,068
Come on, man!

196
00:19:46,107 --> 00:19:48,098
- You OK?
- No.

197
00:19:51,913 --> 00:19:54,507
That's quite an arm
you got there.

198
00:19:54,582 --> 00:19:57,415
Yeah. Who knew?

199
00:19:59,420 --> 00:20:01,786
So, uh, what's with the UFO thing?

200
00:20:03,524 --> 00:20:04,889
I know it's your first day and all,

201
00:20:04,959 --> 00:20:07,553
but, uh, sooner or later
you'll figure it out.

202
00:20:08,629 --> 00:20:09,755
Figure what out?

203
00:20:10,932 --> 00:20:13,366
I'm definitely not the guy
you want to hang with.

204
00:21:09,156 --> 00:21:11,215
Invisible.

205
00:21:11,259 --> 00:21:13,227
You heard me
when I said that, right?

206
00:21:13,261 --> 00:21:17,357
Yeah. Yeah, because
I remember you being there.

207
00:22:02,376 --> 00:22:06,278
<i>Let us face,
without panic, the reality of our times.</i>

208
00:22:06,314 --> 00:22:08,214
<i>The fact that atom bombs</i>

209
00:22:08,249 --> 00:22:12,447
<i>may, some day, be dropped on our cities.
And let us prepare for survival</i>

210
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:14,545
<i>by understanding the weapon
that threatens us.</i>

211
00:22:14,589 --> 00:22:15,613
Yeah.

212
00:22:21,862 --> 00:22:25,320
How you settling in, bro?

213
00:22:26,567 --> 00:22:29,627
- Fine, thanks.
- Good. That's good.

214
00:22:29,670 --> 00:22:33,037
I see you and Spock are vibing.

215
00:22:33,107 --> 00:22:35,041
Got a bit of a soft spot
for freaks, do you?

216
00:22:35,109 --> 00:22:36,838
Who's talking?

217
00:22:38,879 --> 00:22:41,848
Yikes.

218
00:22:41,916 --> 00:22:45,909
Look. It's cute, it really is.
You are an adorable young man.

219
00:22:45,953 --> 00:22:48,148
But I find it irritating,

220
00:22:48,222 --> 00:22:50,349
so keep it on the bleachers, OK?

221
00:22:50,424 --> 00:22:52,517
- All right.
- Good. That's good.

222
00:22:52,593 --> 00:22:54,254
Also, while I'm here,

223
00:22:54,295 --> 00:22:55,922
I'm gonna let you in on a little tip.

224
00:23:11,479 --> 00:23:15,210
Find your place fast.
Catch the rest of this flick, OK?

225
00:23:15,282 --> 00:23:17,375
Jesus, dude.
You are soaking wet.

226
00:23:46,847 --> 00:23:48,906
John, get up.
Come on. We gotta go.

227
00:23:48,983 --> 00:23:50,007
John.

228
00:23:50,051 --> 00:23:52,576
- John.
- My hands. What...?

229
00:23:52,653 --> 00:23:54,917
- Henri. My hands burn!
- John...

230
00:23:54,989 --> 00:23:56,923
- Look at me and relax.
- What's happening to me?

231
00:23:56,991 --> 00:23:58,549
They called them legacies back home.

232
00:23:58,626 --> 00:24:01,254
You, the nine,
you're the only ones who have them.

233
00:24:01,328 --> 00:24:02,659
- Legacies?
- That's right.

234
00:24:02,697 --> 00:24:04,722
Your parents were members
of the Lorien Garde.

235
00:24:04,765 --> 00:24:07,256
You've inherited their abilities. Gifts.

236
00:24:07,334 --> 00:24:08,460
- Gifts?
- That's right.

237
00:24:08,536 --> 00:24:10,333
My hands light up like road flares.

238
00:24:10,371 --> 00:24:12,931
- And you call that a gift?
- Each legacy has its own function.

239
00:24:13,007 --> 00:24:15,032
There's...
There's more coming?

240
00:24:15,076 --> 00:24:19,740
As you breathe and focus,
you're gonna learn to control them.

241
00:24:19,780 --> 00:24:23,682
- OK. OK.
- Just like you're doing, right now.

242
00:24:23,718 --> 00:24:26,050
OK?

243
00:24:27,254 --> 00:24:28,414
How do your hands feel?

244
00:24:29,523 --> 00:24:33,584
- Better.
