00:48:58,591 --> 00:49:00,149
Who knows?

501
00:49:02,261 --> 00:49:05,094
So, I guess I'll just...

502
00:49:05,164 --> 00:49:07,029
...see you when I see you?

503
00:49:08,267 --> 00:49:09,529
Yeah.

504
00:49:12,138 --> 00:49:13,503
OK.

505
00:49:20,346 --> 00:49:22,439
Your hand's really warm.

506
00:49:39,031 --> 00:49:40,965
All I think about is you.

507
00:49:41,033 --> 00:49:43,661
All I think about is you, too.

508
00:50:07,593 --> 00:50:09,356
Where did you come from?

509
00:50:11,897 --> 00:50:14,297
All right, Mom! I got it!

510
00:50:22,908 --> 00:50:25,001
- I, uh...
- Yeah, I should go.

511
00:50:34,620 --> 00:50:35,598
Bye.

512
00:51:34,213 --> 00:51:37,341
John! In here.

513
00:51:40,286 --> 00:51:41,913
So, what are you?

514
00:51:44,457 --> 00:51:47,654
You threw those football players
around like it was nothing.

515
00:51:47,693 --> 00:51:51,561
And the hand thing?
That's not human.

516
00:51:51,630 --> 00:51:54,929
So I'm asking you, what are you?

517
00:51:57,570 --> 00:51:59,128
Do I need to threaten you?

518
00:51:59,205 --> 00:52:01,571
All right, 'cause I got
some pictures on my phone,

519
00:52:01,640 --> 00:52:03,039
and they're gonna start
some major questions.

520
00:52:03,075 --> 00:52:05,043
- Give me that.
- No.

521
00:52:05,077 --> 00:52:07,409
You know I can hurt you. Hm?

522
00:52:23,929 --> 00:52:26,159
Knock yourself out.

523
00:52:33,339 --> 00:52:36,365
My entire childhood...

524
00:52:37,443 --> 00:52:39,070
<i>...has been an episode of X- Files.</i>

525
00:52:42,081 --> 00:52:44,572
You know what it's like
to feel something...

526
00:52:45,684 --> 00:52:48,448
...so strong...

527
00:52:48,487 --> 00:52:50,421
...that every day you have
to keep telling yourself

528
00:52:50,456 --> 00:52:53,584
your dad's gonna come back
and take you away from this shithole.

529
00:52:53,626 --> 00:52:56,322
And that everything
we believed in was true.

530
00:52:56,395 --> 00:52:58,863
And that we were not crazy.

531
00:53:03,269 --> 00:53:04,293
Please.

532
00:53:09,708 --> 00:53:11,198
Please.

533
00:53:14,814 --> 00:53:16,145
Your dad was right.

534
00:53:17,917 --> 00:53:19,145
What?

535
00:53:25,291 --> 00:53:26,849
He was right.

536
00:53:29,195 --> 00:53:31,425
About ancient astronauts...

537
00:53:32,398 --> 00:53:34,958
...life on other planets...

538
00:53:37,269 --> 00:53:38,566
...all of it.

539
00:53:42,942 --> 00:53:46,469
Yes! I knew... I knew he
wouldn't just leave us!

540
00:53:46,512 --> 00:53:50,471
I mean, they found his truck near the
border of Mexico, and he was just gone.

541
00:53:50,516 --> 00:53:52,347
- Maybe they took him.
- Sam...

542
00:53:52,418 --> 00:53:54,716
If he knew you were here,
he'd come home.

543
00:53:54,787 --> 00:53:58,120
- You can't tell anyone.
- No, I-I-I wouldn't.

544
00:53:58,157 --> 00:54:00,352
No, no, no. You gotta promise me.
Nobody knows this.

545
00:54:00,426 --> 00:54:04,556
There are others from where I'm from
looking for me.

546
00:54:04,630 --> 00:54:06,928
I'm not safe.

547
00:54:06,999 --> 00:54:11,936
Sam! I know you are in there.
Get your ass in the house, now!

548
00:54:13,038 --> 00:54:14,471
Wait until I get inside and then go.

549
00:54:14,507 --> 00:54:16,236
Sam?

550
00:54:18,244 --> 00:54:19,472
I promise.

551
00:54:22,047 --> 00:54:24,743
Yes!

552
00:54:27,820 --> 00:54:29,344
Come on.

553
00:54:43,836 --> 00:54:45,736
Hey, you maniac.

554
00:54:45,804 --> 00:54:49,171
- Hello, son.
- Hey, what's with the, uh...?

555
00:54:53,612 --> 00:54:54,601
Hello, Dad.

556
00:54:54,680 --> 00:54:56,739
Sheriff James says
some boys got hurt last night.

557
00:54:56,815 --> 00:54:58,874
Couple of them
spent the night in the hospital.

558
00:54:58,918 --> 00:55:00,408
- You said it was four?
- Yeah, four.

559
00:55:00,486 --> 00:55:03,512
- On the football team.
- Yeah, that's right.

560
00:55:03,556 --> 00:55:07,890
Of course, none of them are talking.
That includes my own boy, Mark.

561
00:55:09,595 --> 00:55:13,725
- Your son is Mark?
- Yeah, that's right.

562
00:55:13,766 --> 00:55:15,791
You know, that was his
throwing arm that got hurt.

563
00:55:15,868 --> 00:55:17,859
He said you were there.

564
00:55:20,105 --> 00:55:22,596
Uh, no. I was actually with a girl.

565
00:55:22,641 --> 00:55:26,737
So I wasn't paying any attention.
Um...

566
00:55:26,779 --> 00:55:27,803
Sarah Hart?

567
00:55:31,517 --> 00:55:36,079
Well, no one wants to be the first
one to say what really happened.

568
00:55:36,121 --> 00:55:39,613
But, eventually, someone will.

569
00:55:39,658 --> 00:55:42,354
I'm sure you're right.
Thank you, Sheriff.

570
00:55:42,428 --> 00:55:44,794
If we hear anything,
we'll let you know.

571
00:56:05,017 --> 00:56:07,679
- Four of them, huh?
- Yeah.

572
00:56:09,288 --> 00:56:11,051
Was it difficult?

573
00:56:11,924 --> 00:56:13,983
Piece of cake.

574
00:56:14,026 --> 00:56:16,654
Good. Means you're getting it.

575
00:56:16,695 --> 00:56:18,720
Go upstairs, pack your stuff.

576
00:56:18,797 --> 00:56:20,162
Because of last night?

577
00:56:20,232 --> 00:56:22,826
Because I don't like people
showing up asking questions.

578
00:56:22,901 --> 00:56:25,927
- And I think this is gonna raise a few.
- "They walk among us."

579
00:56:25,971 --> 00:56:27,871
What is this? Some more
"truth is out there" freaks?

580
00:56:27,940 --> 00:56:30,841
Except that's actually you.

581
00:56:30,909 --> 00:56:33,070
One of the kids must
have caught you on video.

582
00:56:33,145 --> 00:56:34,544
Oh, shit.

583
00:56:34,613 --> 00:56:36,672
<i>He's some kind of freak!</i>

584
00:56:36,715 --> 00:56:38,012
I can't get through the firewall.

585
00:56:38,050 --> 00:56:39,847
We have to go there
and take it down ourselves.

586
00:56:39,918 --> 00:56:42,045
Mogs see this, just a matter of time.

587
00:56:42,121 --> 00:56:44,419
Pack your stuff. We're leaving.

588
00:56:45,791 --> 00:56:47,554
I'm not going.

589
00:56:48,927 --> 00:56:50,724
I'm sorry, what did you say?

590
00:56:51,830 --> 00:56:53,491
I'm not going.

591
00:56:53,532 --> 00:56:56,763
OK. If you want to pick
the next place, that's fine...

592
00:56:56,835 --> 00:56:58,530
It's not my fight and it never was!

593
00:56:58,604 --> 00:57:00,868
I can't even remember
a world before this one.

594
00:57:00,939 --> 00:57:02,770
Wait, wait...

595
00:57:02,841 --> 00:57:05,173
...is this because of a girl?

596
00:57:07,012 --> 00:57:09,003
Go upstairs and get your stuff.

597
00:57:10,182 --> 00:57:13,379
- You're not my father.
- No, no, no. He's dead.

598
00:57:13,419 --> 00:57:16,252
He died for you.
In fact, you know what?

599
00:57:16,321 --> 00:57:20,223
You have no idea how many others
have made sacrifices so you could live!

600
00:57:20,292 --> 00:57:21,782
And it wasn't so you could come here

601
00:57:21,860 --> 00:57:24,021
and experience puppy love
like a real live boy!

602
00:57:24,063 --> 00:57:25,758
I'm not leaving.

603
00:57:28,567 --> 00:57:31,434
John... John!

604
00:57:31,503 --> 00:57:32,765
I'm not leaving!

605
00:57:34,039 --> 00:57:37,600
Oh, yeah, I can do that now.

606
00:57:43,882 --> 00:57:45,042
Hey, John!

607
00:57:56,028 --> 00:57:58,462
I'm letting go, OK?

608
00:57:59,598 --> 00:58:01,361
- OK?
- OK.

609
00:58:12,344 --> 00:58:15,438
- On our planet...
- Just tell me why they want to kill me.

610
00:58:15,481 --> 00:58:19,975
The Mogs, they don't colonize.
They decimate. And then they move on.

611
00:58:20,052 --> 00:58:22,748
And now, they've moved here.

612
00:58:22,788 --> 00:58:27,725
There are few forces that can stop them.
You and the other five can.

613
00:58:27,760 --> 00:58:29,421
You were saved for a bigger purpose.

614
00:58:29,461 --> 00:58:33,124
I'm not gonna let you throw that away
for a girl.

615
00:58:33,165 --> 00:58:35,633
She's not just a girl.

616
00:58:38,170 --> 00:58:40,297
I think about leaving her...

617
00:58:40,939 --> 00:58:42,930
...but I can't.

618
00:58:42,975 --> 00:58:45,409
And I don't know why.

619
00:58:49,381 --> 00:58:53,283
We don't love like the humans.
With us, it's forever.

620
00:58:57,389 --> 00:58:59,220
You never forget.

621
00:59:01,727 --> 00:59:06,164
If she is that for you,
then don't let them win.

622
00:59:06,198 --> 00:59:08,564
Or you'll never forgive yourself.

623
00:59:11,670 --> 00:59:12,694
Now, we have to go.

624
00:59:14,006 --> 00:59:16,668
I'll take care of the website tonight.
Buy you a day.

625
00:59:16,742 --> 00:59:20,576
A day? To say goodbye?

626
00:59:20,646 --> 00:59:22,876
That's more than the rest of us had.

627
00:59:41,366 --> 00:59:43,266
<i>He's some kind of freak!</i>

628
00:59:53,879 --> 00:59:56,575
Henri, I'm going to Sarah's.

629
01:00:00,519 --> 01:00:01,543
Henri?

630
01:00:22,841 --> 01:00:25,605
Henri? Hello? Henri?

631
01:00:25,677 --> 01:00:30,307
<i>No, but come here
and I'll tell you how to find him.</i>

632
01:00:30,382 --> 01:00:32,179
Who are you? Where's Henri?

633
01:00:32,217 --> 01:00:35,118
<i>417 Willard Court,
Warsaw, Indiana.</i>

634
01:00:45,931 --> 01:00:48,229
Come on, come on.

635
01:00:48,267 --> 01:00:49,791
I need your help.

636
01:00:54,973 --> 01:00:56,804
So, you guys... you guys don't...

637
01:00:56,875 --> 01:00:59,207
- Abduct people?
- Yeah.

638
01:00:59,244 --> 01:01:00,268
No.

639
01:01:00,312 --> 01:01:03,770
But the other guys,
the ones that are chasing you...

640
01:01:03,849 --> 01:01:05,009
...they do?

641
01:01:26,405 --> 01:01:27,895
That's it.

642
01:01:29,775 --> 01:01:31,106
Thanks.

643
01:01:38,884 --> 01:01:41,375
Whoa! You brought a gun?

644
01:01:41,453 --> 01:01:44,445
I stole it from Ed.
It might come in handy. Let's go.

645
01:01:44,523 --> 01:01:47,856
- No.
- Dude, I came here to help you.

646
01:01:47,926 --> 01:01:51,453
You have. Now, go home.

647
01:02:09,715 --> 01:02:11,376
Whoa!

648
01:02:14,119 --> 01:02:16,178
- What are you doing?
- I'm not bailing.

649
01:02:16,254 --> 01:02:17,983
What if these Mog people took my dad?

650
01:02:50,022 --> 01:02:54,459
Holy shit!

651
01:02:54,526 --> 01:02:56,687
But you just dead-bolted it.

652
01:02:58,196 --> 01:03:00,892
- OK. New plan.
- Yeah.

653
01:03:00,966 --> 01:03:04,060
You follow that guy and you
text me if he comes back, OK?

654
01:03:04,102 --> 01:03:05,933
Copy that. I'm on it.

655
01:04:40,165 --> 01:04:41,189
Henri.

656
01:04:55,647 --> 01:04:57,444
- Are you OK?
- You're not supposed to be here.

657
01:04:57,482 --> 01:04:59,643
- What happened?
- The Mogs set this up.

658
01:04:59,684 --> 01:05:02,517
We need to leave. They're coming.

659
01:05:02,554 --> 01:05:05,523
Everybody stays right where they are
or I'll shoot this kid.

660
01:05:05,557 --> 01:05:08,151
I'll do it!
Get your hands up!

661
01:05:08,193 --> 01:05:09,490
So glad you brought the gun.

662
01:05:10,862 --> 01:05:12,193
You're Malcolm's boy.

663
01:05:13,532 --> 01:05:16,797
- Get the lights, will you?
- Shut up! Get your hands up!

664
01:05:22,674 --> 01:05:23,698
Oh!

665
01:05:28,847 --> 01:05:32,374
You! You're the one
from the video on our site.

666
01:05:32,450 --> 01:05:35,510
- The one they're after.
- The one who's after?

667
01:05:35,554 --> 01:05:38,352
- What's he talking about?
- The Mogs, they've been here.

668
01:05:38,390 --> 01:05:39,721
- This was a trap.
- Yeah.

669
01:05:39,791 --> 01:05:43,227
These dudes, whatever they are, man,
they got plans, know what I'm sayin'?

670
01:05:43,261 --> 01:05:45,559
- John...
- I'm that guy, the conspiracy guy.

671
01:05:45,597 --> 01:05:48,532
Nobody gives a crap what I say.
But this is real, man!

672
01:05:48,567 --> 01:05:49,966
John. It's time to leave.

673
01:05:50,035 --> 01:05:53,732
They like it here, Earth. They're gonna
take all this shit, everything!

674
01:05:53,805 --> 01:05:55,102
John! Now!

675
01:05:55,173 --> 01:05:57,198
We either do what they say
or we are all gonna die.

676
01:05:57,242 --> 01:05:59,710
It's time to go! Now!

677
01:06:15,694 --> 01:06:18,788
John. John! John, no!

678
01:06:53,231 --> 01:06:55,096
John, go!

679
01:06:55,133 --> 01:06:56,600
- Now!
- Go!

680
01:07:22,761 --> 01:07:25,286
Start the car.
Come on! Get us out of here!

681
01:07:25,330 --> 01:07:27,025
- I can't find the keys!
- What do you mean?

682
01:07:27,098 --> 01:07:29,589
- I can't find the keys!
- Come on! Come on!

683
01:07:30,435 --> 01:07:32,665
Guys, what are we waiting for?

684
01:07:34,506 --> 01:07:36,406
- I've lost the keys!
- John, start the engine.

685
01:07:36,474 --> 01:07:39,602
- What?
- You can do it. Start the car.

686
01:07:42,380 --> 01:07:44,610
- Come on.
- Start the car.

687
01:07:51,356 --> 01:07:53,551
Whoa, whoa. Come on, come on!
He's coming! He's coming!

688
01:07:53,625 --> 01:07:55,024
Start the car! Start the car!

689
01:07:55,060 --> 01:07:57,961
Use your magic powers!
Come on! We are so dead!

690
01:07:59,464 --> 01:08:02,024
Oh, my God!

691
01:08:06,004 --> 01:08:08,234
Go! Drive the car!

692
01:08:19,851 --> 01:08:21,546
You take this.

693
01:08:26,891 --> 01:08:29,359
Malcolm was using it
to track the others.

694
01:08:29,394 --> 01:08:32,659
- Wait. So, my dad was...
- He was helping us.

695
01:08:32,697 --> 01:08:34,892
He was supposed to bring us together.

696
01:08:36,701 --> 01:08:38,032
You need to find the others.

697
01:08:38,970 --> 01:08:40,460
Together you'll be more powerful.

698
01:08:53,017 --> 01:08:54,917
I can't do this without you.

699
01:08:57,021 --> 01:08:58,283
Yes, you can.

700
01:08:59,991 --> 01:09:01,686
Yes, you can.

701
01:09:03,795 --> 01:09:07,754
You have no idea
what you're capable of.

702
01:09:14,005 --> 01:09:15,029
Henri.

703
01:10:10,995 --> 01:10:12,428
Just let me talk.

704
01:10:14,098 --> 01:10:16,760
OK. So, I called you like you said.

705
01:10:18,670 --> 01:10:21,036
I mean, it's not my fault they got...

706
01:10:22,807 --> 01:10:24,798
I mean, we held up our end.

707
01:10:24,843 --> 01:10:27,334
- Hm.
- We're still in?

708
01:10:27,412 --> 01:10:30,711
The whole new world order thing?

709
01:10:30,782 --> 01:10:34,775
The Locator.

710
01:10:34,819 --> 01:10:37,481
- Where is it?
- OK.

711
01:10:37,522 --> 01:10:41,686
All he had was a knife and that rock.

712
01:10:43,027 --> 01:10:44,119
And I put it...

713
01:10:46,231 --> 01:10:50,600
- It was over there, man.
- "It was over there, man."

714
01:10:50,668 --> 01:10:52,727
But it's not there now.

715
01:11:14,993 --> 01:11:19,225
Cartoons for children.

716
01:11:19,264 --> 01:11:21,858
Where I'm from, men have to work.

717
01:11:21,900 --> 01:11:23,765
Look, I'll work hard.

718
01:11:23,835 --> 01:11:27,498
The disregard that so many of you
have for practical matters,

719
01:11:27,539 --> 01:11:32,101
it's... beautiful.

720
01:11:32,176 --> 01:11:34,303
I think we should
all have some fun. Huh?

721
01:11:36,247 --> 01:11:39,307
Gadgets.
You call them "toys for boys."

722
01:11:40,852 --> 01:11:42,615
I have a gadget.

723
01:11:42,687 --> 01:11:46,555
- Would you like to play with it?
- Uh... No, no. I...

724
01:11:46,591 --> 01:11:50,994
It wants to play with you!

725
01:12:04,642 --> 01:12:05,904
Need to talk to you.

726
01:12:05,944 --> 01:12:07,935
Any idea where
I might find your friend?

727
01:12:07,979 --> 01:12:10,607
He's not who you think he is.

728
01:12:10,648 --> 01:12:12,479
Excuse me?

729
01:12:17,956 --> 01:12:19,548
<i>The Paradise Sheriff's Department</i>

730
01:12:19,591 --> 01:12:21,286
<i>raided the home of two suspects,</i>

731
01:12:21,326 --> 01:12:24,090
<i>seizing computers
and several suspicious items.</i>

732
01:12:24,128 --> 01:12:27,461
<i>An APB has been issued on
the suspects and anyone with...</i>

733
01:12:30,935 --> 01:12:32,459
We need to get out of here.

734
01:12:34,238 --> 01:12:35,933
There's a news thing.

735
01:12:35,974 --> 01:12:39,137
The cops think you and Henri
are criminals or terrorists.

736
01:12:49,887 --> 01:12:51,479
We're going back.

737
01:12:54,692 --> 01:12:56,660
I'm outside of
the home here in Warsaw

738
01:12:56,694 --> 01:12:59,857
where the mutilated bodies of
two paranormal website operators

739
01:12:59,931 --> 01:13:01,956
were just found a few hours ago.

740
01:13:02,000 --> 01:13:03,797
The police are not saying
if they have any leads

741
01:13:03,835 --> 01:13:06,201
or even why these
brutal murders occurred.

742
01:13:06,270 --> 01:13:08,602
Police have no suspects
at this time...

743
01:13:19,317 --> 01:13:20,807
- I have one of those!
- What?

744
01:13:20,852 --> 01:13:23,616
One of those.
I took it from my dad's stash.

745
01:13:23,655 --> 01:13:25,850
- I need you to get it.
- Yeah, yeah.

746
01:13:25,923 --> 01:13:29,415
Let me off at Linndale.
Sarah's at a house up there.

747
01:13:29,494 --> 01:13:31,428
I'll call you after.

748
01:13:31,496 --> 01:13:33,862
- And then what?
- Then I get the rock and you go home.

749
01:13:44,909 --> 01:13:47,036
- It's him.
- John?

750
01:13:47,645 --> 01:13:50,978
- Did you see that?
- What's he doing here?

751
01:13:52,550 --> 01:13:53,676
Yeah, he's here.

752
01:13:58,423 --> 01:13:59,583
That's him!

753
01:14:15,973 --> 01:14:17,600
Come on.

754
01:14:19,110 --> 01:14:20,270
Come on.

755
01:14:43,201 --> 01:14:45,692
Doesn't seem like your kind of crowd.

756
01:14:48,606 --> 01:14:51,769
Not so sure who my
kind of crowd is right now.

757
01:14:51,809 --> 01:14:54,403
- Look, just...
- John Smith?

758
01:14:54,445 --> 01:14:56,379
I'm such an idiot.

759
01:14:57,749 --> 01:15:00,980
And they're saying that your dad
is some kind of terrorist.

760
01:15:01,052 --> 01:15:03,179
He's not a terrorist.

761
01:15:03,788 --> 01:15:05,187
Tell me the truth.

762
01:15:06,157 --> 01:15:08,387
Who are you?

763
01:15:18,836 --> 01:15:20,098
He's upstairs.

764
01:15:20,938 --> 01:15:22,735
All right, guys, out of the way.

765
01:15:24,709 --> 01:15:26,939
You didn't answer my question.

766
01:15:27,812 --> 01:15:29,439
I just came to say goodbye.

767
01:15:29,480 --> 01:15:31,448
- John, wait! What are you... No, John!
- Don't move!

768
01:15:31,482 --> 01:15:33,882
Sarah!

769
01:15:43,094 --> 01:15:44,118
How...

770
01:15:44,162 --> 01:15:45,629
- Move! Move!
- Go!

771
01:16:01,312 --> 01:16:02,973
That was awesome!

772
01:16:03,014 --> 01:16:06,450
Whoa...

773
01:16:12,089 --> 01:16:13,989
What you did is not possible.

774
01:16:14,025 --> 01:16:15,549
Who I am...

775
01:16:15,626 --> 01:16:17,594
...it's all in here.
I took these for you.

776
01:16:17,662 --> 01:16:21,393
Wait. Come with me.
Please.

777
01:16:22,333 --> 01:16:24,699
Any idea where they'd be?

778
01:16:24,769 --> 01:16:27,203
I think I know
where she might go.

779
01:16:37,248 --> 01:16:40,684
- Who the hell are they?
- Big-ass linebackers?

780
01:16:48,993 --> 01:16:51,188
Holy shit...

781
01:16:55,199 --> 01:16:56,962
No, no, no!

782
01:16:59,670 --> 01:17:00,762
Dad!

783
01:17:13,251 --> 01:17:17,085
An alcohol-fuelled
young guy like you...

784
01:17:17,154 --> 01:17:20,988
...healthy and well-fed.

785
01:17:21,058 --> 01:17:24,653
I bet you watch a lot of television,
don't you? Do you? Do you?

786
01:17:24,729 --> 01:17:26,924
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

787
01:17:26,964 --> 01:17:29,524
In this situation here,
you're probably thinking,

788
01:17:29,567 --> 01:17:32,764
"Maybe I could save the day.
Maybe I could be the hero."

789
01:17:32,837 --> 01:17:37,069
But I say... don't do that.

790
01:17:37,108 --> 01:17:38,803
OK?

791
01:17:40,511 --> 01:17:43,742
Tell me now, where is the boy?

792
01:18:11,309 --> 01:18:13,834
These are beautiful.

793
01:18:28,459 --> 01:18:29,983
Can you show me?

794
01:18:57,822 --> 01:19:00,188
- No!
- Get in!

795
01:19:04,395 --> 01:19:07,887
Let me go! Let me go!

796
01:19:12,670 --> 01:19:13,898
Let go of me!

797
01:19:21,479 --> 01:19:23,379
- Hello?
- Where are you?

798
01:19:23,414 --> 01:19:24,506
I'm at the high school.

799
01:19:24,548 --> 01:19:26,311
<i>Yeah, you need to get out of there now.</i>

800
01:19:26,350 --> 01:19:27,374
Why? What's happening?

801
01:19:27,418 --> 01:19:30,216
Your stunt with the car
is already on YouTube.

802
01:19:30,287 --> 01:19:31,686
<i>If they're not right on your ass now,</i>

803
01:19:31,722 --> 01:19:33,451
<i>they will be soon.</i>

804
01:19:34,025 --> 01:19:35,390
Come on.

805
01:19:35,426 --> 01:19:37,587
And don't tell me this is not my fight.

806
01:19:37,661 --> 01:19:42,098
My dad probably knew those guys were
coming and that's why they took him.

807
01:19:42,733 --> 01:19:45,725
And also, I have your dog.

808
01:19:46,570 --> 01:19:47,730
<i>Look, I'm on my way.</i>

809
01:19:47,772 --> 01:19:49,262
<i>I'll meet you out front of the school.</i>

810
01:19:49,340 --> 01:19:51,205
<i>You've got to get out now.</i>

811
01:19:51,776 --> 01:19:53,368
<i>John?</i>

812
01:19:53,411 --> 01:19:54,469
<i>John!</i>

813
01:19:59,116 --> 01:20:00,447
Let's go.

814
01:20:04,021 --> 01:20:07,252
Let go of me!

815
01:20:11,228 --> 01:20:13,753
Jesus!

816
01:20:13,798 --> 01:20:17,598
Sarah! If you're in there, run!

817
01:20:17,668 --> 01:20:20,398
Run!

818
01:20:23,941 --> 01:20:26,910
Let me go!

819
01:20:32,750 --> 01:20:35,651
Listen to me. I'm not gonna
let them hurt you, OK?

820
01:20:35,719 --> 01:20:38,381
Do you understand me?
Come on.

821
01:21:52,163 --> 01:21:55,155
Lt'd be a good idea, cowboy, if you
kept your heroics off the Internet.

822
01:21:57,501 --> 01:22:01,733
- Who are you?
- Number Six. Where's your protector?

823
01:22:01,805 --> 01:22:05,206
- Dead.
- Yeah. Mine, too.

824
01:22:05,242 --> 01:22:06,675
Mogs got her four months ago.

825
01:22:06,710 --> 01:22:09,270
- We've been tracking them down.
- Tracking them?

826
01:22:09,346 --> 01:22:11,576
Yeah. Lucky for you, I saved your ass.

827
01:22:11,649 --> 01:22:13,879
You should be watching your own ass.

828
01:22:13,918 --> 01:22:16,216
Mogs have all the exits covered.

829
01:22:16,253 --> 01:22:19,245
Looks like you're gonna
have to fight to get out.

830
01:22:19,323 --> 01:22:21,553
- Are you game?
- Yeah.

831
01:22:21,592 --> 01:22:24,026
There's a tunnel under the school
that leads to the stadium.

832
01:22:24,061 --> 01:22:26,825
Oh, you made friends.
How nice.

833
01:22:28,899 --> 01:22:30,196
Let's go.

834
01:22:31,468 --> 01:22:34,062
Got any other legacies
I should know about?

835
01:22:34,138 --> 01:22:35,696
Stay tuned.

836
01:23:07,871 --> 01:23:10,339
Oh, shit.

837
01:23:17,781 --> 01:23:19,214
Oh, shit!

838
01:23:28,959 --> 01:23:30,790
Careful, they'll see us.

839
01:23:32,096 --> 01:23:33,996
And you're going
to need all your energy.

840
01:23:38,102 --> 01:23:41,094
- What was that?
- They're comin'.

841
01:23:41,138 --> 01:23:43,606
Ah! Whoa, whoa, whoa!

842
01:23:43,641 --> 01:23:46,132
Whoa! Sam, what are you doing?

843
01:23:46,210 --> 01:23:47,575
Did you see what just
flew out of that truck?

844
01:23:47,611 --> 01:23:49,806
And your dog just shape-shifted
into one of them.

845
01:23:49,880 --> 01:23:53,008
I thought he was gonna eat me.
Here's your rock.

846
01:23:55,085 --> 01:23:59,021
Hi! I'm Sam. What's your name?

847
01:24:00,024 --> 01:24:01,252
Jane Doe.

848
01:24:01,292 --> 01:24:02,589
That's cool. It's cool.

849
01:24:02,626 --> 01:24:03,991
So, are you a number, too?

850
01:24:04,028 --> 01:24:07,020
- Who is this tool?
- Sam, focus.

851
01:24:07,097 --> 01:24:09,657
What flew out of the truck?

852
01:24:13,771 --> 01:24:16,331
Come on! Go, go!

853
01:24:16,373 --> 01:24:19,672
Sam. Come on! Go!

854
01:24:23,947 --> 01:24:25,710
Come on! Come on!

855
01:24:28,819 --> 01:24:31,151
Come on!

856
01:25:31,181 --> 01:25:32,273
Ahh!

857
01:25:39,923 --> 01:25:42,255
- Hit me.
- What?

858
01:25:42,326 --> 01:25:44,726
With your lumen.
I need to power-up.

859
01:25:46,930 --> 01:25:48,295
Hit me!

860
01:25:59,276 --> 01:26:01,107
Red Bull's for pussies.

861
01:26:03,447 --> 01:26:05,574
He killed Henri. I want him.

862
01:26:37,281 --> 01:26:40,341
Ah!

863
01:26:42,152 --> 01:26:43,551
Four!

864
01:26:55,766 --> 01:26:57,859
You're good with your hands.

865
01:26:57,935 --> 01:26:59,903
- Thanks.
- No problem.

866
01:27:01,405 --> 01:27:05,705
- My dog, he, uh... he just...
- Yeah, he's a chimera.

867
01:27:05,776 --> 01:27:07,903
He came with you from Lorien.

868
01:27:07,978 --> 01:27:10,378
Someone had to look after you.

869
01:28:13,477 --> 01:28:15,570
You brought a gun?
Are you serious?

870
01:28:15,612 --> 01:28:18,046
- What? It might come in handy.
- This way.

871
01:28:28,759 --> 01:28:29,783
Go!

872
01:28:38,769 --> 01:28:40,396
- Take her back to the tunnel!
- Got it! Come on!

873
01:28:47,744 --> 01:28:49,974
- Holy...!
- Ahh!

874
01:28:54,585 --> 01:28:55,882
I play a lot of Xbox.

875
01:29:02,192 --> 01:29:03,216
Oh!

876
01:29:23,480 --> 01:29:25,641
Oh! Ahh!

877
01:30:35,485 --> 01:30:39,751
Number Four, I think you
have something I need. Hm?

878
01:30:41,358 --> 01:30:45,727
Oh, thank you for making
this so nice and easy.

879
01:30:45,762 --> 01:30:51,029
Think of how quickly we'll finish off
the rest of the planet. It's fantastic!

880
01:30:51,768 --> 01:30:54,396
Soon, I'll be done with all of you.

881
01:30:54,438 --> 01:30:56,702
Just relax.

882
01:30:58,108 --> 01:31:01,874
You can't stop what's coming.
You never could.

883
01:31:01,912 --> 01:31:04,005
You have...

884
01:31:04,047 --> 01:31:06,481
...no idea...

885
01:31:07,684 --> 01:31:09,151
...what I'm capable of.

886
01:31:25,402 --> 01:31:26,699
Ah!

887
01:32:23,627 --> 01:32:24,821
John.

888
01:32:28,098 --> 01:32:29,793
Fireproof?

889
01:32:30,967 --> 01:32:33,333
I told you to stay tuned.

890
01:33:02,232 --> 01:33:04,359
All right, give me that.
Come on.

891
01:33:05,235 --> 01:33:06,463
Thank you.

892
01:33:37,500 --> 01:33:41,493
Oh. Well, that was disappointing.
So, not a tracking device?

893
01:33:41,538 --> 01:33:43,597
No, it was.

894
01:33:43,673 --> 01:33:46,073
- Did you feel that, too?
- Yeah.

895
01:33:46,142 --> 01:33:49,305
- We know where we need to go.
- Yeah, we can find the others.

896
01:33:55,552 --> 01:33:58,749
- Here.
- Thank you.

897
01:33:59,723 --> 01:34:01,588
I hope this doesn't get you in trouble.

898
01:34:01,625 --> 01:34:06,119
Nah. Stuff goes missing from evidence
all the time.

899
01:34:06,196 --> 01:34:08,596
My dad won't even know.

900
01:34:08,632 --> 01:34:11,533
- You want to be heading west now.
- Why?

901
01:34:11,568 --> 01:34:14,059
Because I told my dad you're going east.

902
01:34:21,978 --> 01:34:25,880
- Six, Sam's coming with us.
- What?

903
01:34:26,983 --> 01:34:28,746
- No way.
- He's one of us now.

904
01:34:28,785 --> 01:34:31,015
We need to find his father.

905
01:34:34,624 --> 01:34:38,025
You slow us down,
I'll shoot you myself.

906
01:34:38,094 --> 01:34:40,562
And I believe you.
Could we go now?

907
01:34:46,536 --> 01:34:48,663
You know, I wouldn't leave
if it wasn't, uh...

908
01:34:48,738 --> 01:34:51,502
- Safer.
- Yeah.

909
01:34:51,574 --> 01:34:53,132
I know.

910
01:34:54,344 --> 01:34:56,812
Really sorry about
what happened with Henri.

911
01:34:58,081 --> 01:34:59,844
Me, too.

912
01:35:03,219 --> 01:35:05,710
You know I'll find you again.

913
01:35:08,024 --> 01:35:11,016
Probably still be here.

914
01:35:12,228 --> 01:35:13,820
It's the people that make the place.

915
01:35:14,597 --> 01:35:16,929
- Right?
- Yeah.

916
01:35:23,273 --> 01:35:27,141
Henri warned me that
we only fall for one person.

917
01:35:29,346 --> 01:35:30,813
Ever?

918
01:35:31,648 --> 01:35:33,081
Ever.

919
01:37:05,875 --> 01:37:08,776
<i>This is the first town
I've left without Henri.</i>

920
01:37:09,712 --> 01:37:13,170
<i>But it's also the first one
I have a reason to come back to.</i>

921
01:37:14,551 --> 01:37:18,043
<i>Henri was right,
we're stronger together.</i>

922
01:37:18,588 --> 01:37:21,182
<i>So we will find the others.</i>

923
01:37:23,426 --> 01:37:28,056
<i>My planet is called Lorien,
but Earth is my home now.</i>

924
01:37:29,099 --> 01:37:32,796
<i>It's as good a place
as any in the universe.</i>

925
01:37:32,836 --> 01:37:35,270
<i>And that's how it's going to stay.</i>

